707140f-b.text:
(1)
2095 Utica Ave., east side, between Aves. M and N, showing the Will Williamson house, which was still standing in 1929. See Van Wyck's
book titled Eeskachauge for further information.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
Another view, showing the rear of the house.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(3)
The same, looking narthward, and showing the garage on the right.
Utica Ave., is seen in the background.
1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(4)
Another view southsard, showing also the rears of houses that face
on East 51st Street.
May 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
